//axhob_operation
{bust_caparison_windows}

NOTE: {busn_caparison} on Windows -- three phases. Phase 1: admin SSH
key trust + `sshd_config` hardening. Phase 2: key-only reconnect.
Phase 3: post-trust admin posture (WSL distribution, powercfg,
Tailscale service). Closes with {bust_invigilate_windows}.

NOTE: Nuclear -- every invocation purges and re-establishes the
caparison-managed posture; no skip-if-present logic.
{bust_handbook_windows} owns operator-manual posture; caparison owns
the idempotent admin-shell remainder.

NOTE: Phase 1's `Restart-Service sshd` terminates its own ssh session
-- the post-restart disconnect is the expected phase boundary, not a
failure. PowerShell-side operations use `Get-Content`, `Set-Service`,
`Start-Service`, `Restart-Service`, `wsl.exe --import`; bash-side
BCG-compliant matching extracts effective `sshd_config` directives
from the raw bytes.

The {busn_caparison} operation on Windows:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
{burn_regime} targets a Windows OpenSSH node.

//axhoq_precondition
{bust_handbook_windows} operator-manual scope is complete -- OpenSSH
Server installed and reachable, security-sensitive registry edits
applied (`DevicePasswordLessBuildVersion`, `PlatformAoAcOverride`),
Tailscale installed + Run-Unattended + first auth, netplwiz
auto-login, and {burp_privileged_user} has a known password.
Caparison presupposes this scope.

//axhoq_precondition
{burp_privileged_user} is in the Administrators group;
{burp_privileged_key_file} is unencrypted.

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — open admin SSH session*:
.. {busc_call}
ssh as {burp_privileged_user} with
`PreferredAuthentications=publickey,password` (steady-state: key via
{burp_privileged_key_file}; first run: TTY password)
.. {busc_store}
`«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»` for phase 1 operations
.. {busc_fatal}
on connection failure -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — derive admin pubkey*:
.. {busc_call}
`ssh-keygen -y` on {burp_privileged_key_file}
.. {busc_store}
`«ADMIN_PUBKEY»` from stdout
.. {busc_fatal}
on derivation failure -- privkey encrypted (unsupported) or unreadable

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — install admin pubkey*:
.. write `«ADMIN_PUBKEY»` to `administrators_authorized_keys` over
`«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»` as a bare key entry (no `command=`)
.. nuclear -- file replaced, not merged
.. {busc_fatal}
on write failure -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — lock down administrators_authorized_keys ACL*:
.. {busc_call}
`icacls` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»` -- ACL restricted to SYSTEM and
Administrators (Windows OpenSSH refuses the file otherwise);
idempotent
.. {busc_fatal}
on `icacls` failure -- phase 2 reconnect would fail

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — write hardened sshd_config directives*:
.. write `PubkeyAuthentication yes`, `PasswordAuthentication no`,
`PermitEmptyPasswords no` to `sshd_config` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»`;
idempotent
.. {busc_fatal}
on write failure -- restart would still serve password auth

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — verify hardened directives took*:
.. {busc_call}
PowerShell `Get-Content` on `sshd_config` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»`
.. {busc_store}
`«SSHD_CONFIG_BYTES»`
.. {busc_require}
`«SSHD_CONFIG_BYTES»` parses to `PubkeyAuthentication yes`,
`PasswordAuthentication no`, `PermitEmptyPasswords no` as effective
directive values (BCG-compliant matching)
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- prior write did not take or stale override shadows

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — validate sshd_config*:
.. {busc_call}
`sshd -t` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»` -- penultimate atomic op of phase 1
.. {busc_store}
`«SSHD_TEST_RESULT»`
.. {busc_require}
`«SSHD_TEST_RESULT»` is zero
.. {busc_fatal}
on non-zero -- aborting preserves the running sshd

//axhos_step
. *Phase 1 — restart sshd*:
.. {busc_call}
`Restart-Service sshd` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P1»` -- final atomic op
of phase 1
.. {busc_fatal}
on invocation failure (the post-restart disconnect itself is the
expected phase boundary)

//axhos_step
. *Phase 2 — reconnect under key-only auth*:
.. {busc_call}
ssh as {burp_privileged_user} with
`PreferredAuthentications=publickey` using {burp_privileged_key_file}
.. {busc_store}
`«ADMIN_SESSION_P2»` for phase 3 operations
.. {busc_fatal}
on reconnect failure -- brick (manual password no longer opens a
session); recover via operator's local console

//axhos_step
. *Phase 3 — stage rbtww-main WSL distribution*:
.. {busc_call}
`wsl.exe --import` from the Ubuntu-24.04 seed over
`«ADMIN_SESSION_P2»` to register `rbtww-main` under the admin user
(canonical: `BUJB_wsl_distribution` in {bujb_jurisdiction})
.. nuclear -- always purge-and-reimport
.. {busc_fatal}
on import failure -- WSL feature disabled, seed unavailable, or
admin user's HKCU\\Lxss state corrupted

//axhos_step
. *Phase 3 — disable powercfg sleep and hibernate*:
.. {busc_call}
`powercfg /change standby-timeout-ac 0`,
`powercfg /change standby-timeout-dc 0`,
`powercfg /hibernate off` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P2»`; idempotent
.. {busc_fatal}
on `powercfg` failure -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope (Modern
Standby AoAc override demotes calls to no-ops)

//axhos_step
. *Phase 3 — set Tailscale service Automatic and running*:
.. {busc_call}
`Set-Service -Name Tailscale -StartupType Automatic` then
`Start-Service -Name Tailscale` over `«ADMIN_SESSION_P2»`; idempotent
.. {busc_fatal}
on `Set-Service` or `Start-Service` failure --
{bust_handbook_windows} scope (install + Run-Unattended + first auth)

//axhos_step
. *Post-completion check — run invigilate-windows*:
.. {busc_call}
{bust_invigilate_windows} for this {burp_investiture}
.. {busc_store}
`«INVIGILATE_RESULT»`
.. {busc_require}
`«INVIGILATE_RESULT»` is zero
.. {busc_fatal}
on non-zero -- invigilate diagnostic surfaced verbatim

//axhog_guarantee
On success:

* Admin SSH is key-only with admin pubkey installed in
  `administrators_authorized_keys` under correct ACLs.
* `sshd_config` carries `PubkeyAuthentication yes`,
  `PasswordAuthentication no`, `PermitEmptyPasswords no`.
* Post-restart admin session authenticates by key alone.
* `rbtww-main` WSL distribution is registered under the admin user.
* `powercfg` sleep and hibernate are disabled.
* Tailscale service is Automatic and running.
* {bust_invigilate_windows} confirms every posture fact end-to-end.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the post-completion {bust_invigilate_windows} passes.
Non-zero on any phase-1 op failure (admin SSH, pubkey, ACL,
`sshd_config`, `sshd -t`), phase-2 reconnect failure, any phase-3 op
failure (`wsl --import`, `powercfg`, Tailscale), or post-completion
invigilate failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_cygwin}

NOTE: {busn_garrison} ceremony with Cygwin bash as the workload shell,
for Windows nodes reached via Cygwin sshd. Workload-only -- garrison
never touches `sshd_config` and never modifies admin authorized_keys.

NOTE: Destruction is letter-agnostic via `zbujb_obliterate_workload`
in {bujb_jurisdiction} -- the single greppable destroy verb. Covenant
spans the Windows SAM entry, `C:\Users\<user>\` profile, the
`C:\cygwin64\home\<user>\` Cygwin home, and the WSL-side
`/home/<user>` inside `rbtww-main` when present. Each step idempotent
on absent state.

NOTE: Admin trust is the responsibility of {busn_caparison} on the
Windows OpenSSH server; Cygwin sshd hardening (when run alongside
Windows OpenSSH) remains operator-manual.

The {busn_garrison} operation on Windows via Cygwin:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
{burn_regime} targets a Windows node with Cygwin sshd installed,
reachable as {burp_privileged_user} under key-only auth using
{burp_privileged_key_file}.

//axhoq_precondition
{busn_caparison} has run for this {burp_investiture} -- admin SSH
trust established by Windows OpenSSH key-only auth.

//axhoq_precondition
{burp_workload_key_file} is unencrypted and exists on the operator's
station.

//axhos_step
. *Assert admin posture*:
.. {busc_call}
{bust_invigilate_windows} for this {burp_investiture}
.. {busc_store}
`«INVIGILATE_RESULT»`
.. {busc_require}
`«INVIGILATE_RESULT»` is zero
.. {busc_fatal}
on non-zero -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope (operator-managed) or
{bust_caparison_windows} scope (caparison-managed); diagnostic
surfaced verbatim

//axhos_step
. *Open admin SSH session*:
.. {busc_call}
ssh as {burp_privileged_user} with {burp_privileged_key_file}; key-auth only
.. {busc_store}
`«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_fatal}
on connection failure -- {bust_caparison_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Obliterate prior workload*:
.. {busc_call}
`zbujb_obliterate_workload` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»` -- single
PowerShell session purges the Windows SAM entry, profile directory,
Cygwin home, and (when `rbtww-main` is installed) the WSL-side Linux
user
.. nuclear -- idempotent on absent state
.. {busc_fatal}
on PowerShell session failure -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Create workload account*:
.. provision {bujb_workload_user} as an unprivileged ssh-only Cygwin
account over `«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_fatal}
on Cygwin account-management failure -- prior obliterate left state

//axhos_step
. *Place workload trust*:
.. {busc_call}
`ssh-keygen -y` on {burp_workload_key_file}
.. {busc_store}
`«WORKLOAD_PUBKEY»` from stdout
.. write `«WORKLOAD_PUBKEY»` to the workload's authorized_keys with
the shell-letter `c` `command=` directive (canonical:
`BUJB_command_c` in {bujb_jurisdiction}):
+
[listing]
----
command="C:/cygwin64/bin/bash --login -c \"$SSH_ORIGINAL_COMMAND\"",no-port-forwarding,no-X11-forwarding,no-agent-forwarding
----
.. {busc_fatal}
on key-write failure -- workload account left without trust

//axhos_step
. *Plant workload key*:
.. copy {burp_workload_key_file} to the workload account at the
shell-letter `c` destination path (canonical: `BUJB_workload_keypath_c`
in {bujb_jurisdiction})
.. {busc_fatal}
on copy failure -- workload account reachable but key absent

//axhos_step
. *Validate round-trip*:
.. {busc_call}
ssh as {bujb_workload_user} with {burp_workload_key_file}; run a
no-op command
.. {busc_store}
`«WORKLOAD_RT_RESULT»`
.. {busc_require}
`«WORKLOAD_RT_RESULT»` is zero
.. {busc_fatal}
on non-zero -- workload trust placed but unreachable

//axhog_guarantee
On success:

* Exactly one workload account named {bujb_workload_user} exists on
  the node, reachable via Cygwin bash.
* Workload authorized_keys carries `«WORKLOAD_PUBKEY»` with the
  shell-letter `c` `command=` directive.
* {burp_workload_key_file} planted at the shell-letter `c` destination
  authenticates the workload round-trip.
* Admin posture is unchanged -- no `sshd_config` writes, no admin
  authorized_keys writes.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the round-trip validation succeeds. Non-zero on
invigilate-windows assertion failure, admin SSH failure, obliterate
failure, Cygwin account-management failure, key-write failure, or
workload round-trip failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_invigilate_windows}

NOTE: {busn_invigilate} on Windows -- read-only host posture
verification. Asserts each posture fact matches expected; no
mutations.

NOTE: Invocation: {bust_caparison_windows} post-completion check;
{bust_garrison_cygwin} and {bust_garrison_wsl} precondition.

NOTE: Failure pointers discriminate operator-managed
({bust_handbook_windows}) from caparison-managed
({bust_caparison_windows}). PowerShell reads via
`Get-ItemPropertyValue`, `Get-Service`, `powercfg /a`, `wsl.exe --list
--quiet`; bash-side BCG-compliant matching extracts each fact.

The {busn_invigilate} operation on Windows:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
{burn_regime} targets a Windows OpenSSH node reachable as
{burp_privileged_user} under key-only auth using
{burp_privileged_key_file}. Admin SSH failure surfaces as the first
posture fact -- invigilate presupposes trust, does not establish it.

//axhos_step
. *Open admin SSH session*:
.. {busc_call}
ssh as {burp_privileged_user} with {burp_privileged_key_file}; key-auth only
.. {busc_store}
`«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_fatal}
on connection failure -- {bust_caparison_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Assert operator-managed registry keys*:
.. For each {bust_handbook_windows}-established registry value
(canonical: `DevicePasswordLessBuildVersion` under
`HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\PasswordLess\Device`):
... {busc_call}
PowerShell `Get-ItemPropertyValue` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»`
... {busc_store}
`«REG_VALUE»`
... {busc_require}
`«REG_VALUE»` matches expected
... {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Assert AoAc override*:
.. {busc_call}
PowerShell `Get-ItemPropertyValue` for
`HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\Power\PlatformAoAcOverride`
.. {busc_store}
`«REG_AOAC»`
.. {busc_require}
`«REG_AOAC»` equals `0`
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope (Modern Standby override)

//axhos_step
. *Assert Tailscale service registered*:
.. {busc_call}
PowerShell `Get-Service Tailscale`
.. {busc_store}
`«SVC_TAILSCALE»`
.. {busc_require}
`«SVC_TAILSCALE»` is non-empty
.. {busc_fatal}
on absence -- {bust_handbook_windows} scope (install + Run-Unattended + first auth)

//axhos_step
. *Assert Tailscale service StartupType*:
.. {busc_call}
PowerShell `Get-Service Tailscale | Select-Object StartType`
.. {busc_store}
`«SVC_STARTTYPE»`
.. {busc_require}
`«SVC_STARTTYPE»` equals `Automatic`
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_caparison_windows} scope

//axhos_step
. *Assert powercfg sleep/hibernate disabled*:
.. {busc_call}
`powercfg /a` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_store}
`«POWERCFG_REPORT»`
.. {busc_require}
`«POWERCFG_REPORT»` reports neither standby nor hibernate as available
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_caparison_windows} scope (or AoAc override missing)

//axhos_step
. *Assert admin's rbtww-main WSL distribution registered*:
.. {busc_call}
`wsl.exe --list --quiet` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_store}
`«WSL_DISTRO_LIST»`
.. {busc_require}
`«WSL_DISTRO_LIST»` contains `rbtww-main` (canonical:
`BUJB_wsl_distribution` in {bujb_jurisdiction})
.. {busc_fatal}
on absence -- {bust_caparison_windows} scope

//axhog_guarantee
On success:

* Every posture fact matches its expected value.
* `«ADMIN_SESSION»` was used only for read commands.
* No mutation occurred.
* The node is in the shape {bust_caparison_windows} produces and
  {bust_garrison_cygwin} / {bust_garrison_wsl} require.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when every posture fact matches expected. Non-zero on first
mismatch with diagnostic naming the failing fact, expected value,
observed value, and pointer ({bust_handbook_windows} for
operator-managed; {bust_caparison_windows} for caparison-managed).

//axhob_operation
{bust_invigilate_macos}

NOTE: {busn_invigilate} on macOS -- read-only host posture
verification. Asserts each posture fact matches expected; no
mutations.

NOTE: Invocation: {bust_caparison_macos} post-completion check;
{bust_garrison_bash} precondition on macOS nodes.

NOTE: Failure pointers discriminate operator-managed
({bust_handbook_macos}) from caparison-managed
({bust_caparison_macos}). Reads via `systemsetup -getremotelogin`,
`pmset -g`, `launchctl list`; bash-side BCG-compliant matching
extracts each fact.

The {busn_invigilate} operation on macOS:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
{burn_regime} targets a macOS node reachable as
{burp_privileged_user} under key-only auth using
{burp_privileged_key_file}. Admin SSH failure surfaces as the first
posture fact -- invigilate presupposes trust, does not establish it.

//axhos_step
. *Open admin SSH session*:
.. {busc_call}
ssh as {burp_privileged_user} with {burp_privileged_key_file}; key-auth only
.. {busc_store}
`«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_fatal}
on connection failure -- {bust_caparison_macos} scope

//axhos_step
. *Assert Remote Login enabled*:
.. {busc_call}
`systemsetup -getremotelogin` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_store}
`«REMOTE_LOGIN_STATE»`
.. {busc_require}
`«REMOTE_LOGIN_STATE»` reports `On`
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_caparison_macos} scope

//axhos_step
. *Assert pmset sleep, displaysleep, and hibernate disabled*:
.. {busc_call}
`pmset -g` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»`
.. {busc_store}
`«PMSET_REPORT»`
.. {busc_require}
`«PMSET_REPORT»` parses to `sleep 0`, `displaysleep 0`, and
`hibernatemode 0` (BCG-compliant matching)
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_caparison_macos} scope

//axhos_step
. *Assert Tailscale launchd service registered*:
.. {busc_call}
`launchctl list` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»` filtered for the tailscaled label
.. {busc_store}
`«SVC_TAILSCALED_MAC»`
.. {busc_require}
`«SVC_TAILSCALED_MAC»` is non-empty
.. {busc_fatal}
on absence -- {bust_handbook_macos} scope (install + first auth)

//axhos_step
. *Assert Tailscale launchd service loaded and running*:
.. {busc_call}
`launchctl list` over `«ADMIN_SESSION»` parsed for PID and last-exit
fields of the tailscaled label
.. {busc_store}
`«SVC_TAILSCALED_STATE»`
.. {busc_require}
`«SVC_TAILSCALED_STATE»` reports a live PID (not `-`)
.. {busc_fatal}
on mismatch -- {bust_caparison_macos} scope (Tailscale launchd auto-start)

//axhog_guarantee
On success:

* Every posture fact matches its expected value.
* `«ADMIN_SESSION»` was used only for read commands.
* No mutation occurred.
* The node is in the shape {bust_caparison_macos} produces and
  {bust_garrison_bash} requires.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when every posture fact matches expected. Non-zero on first
mismatch with diagnostic naming the failing fact, expected value,
observed value, and pointer ({bust_handbook_macos} for
operator-managed; {bust_caparison_macos} for caparison-managed).
